COMMUNITY CONTRIBUTION NOTICE (NON-BINDING)

THE FOLLOWING SECTION IS PURELY INFORMATIONAL AND DOES NOT MODIFY OR LIMIT
THE MIT LICENSE TERMS ABOVE. IT IS A VOLUNTARY COMMUNITY STATEMENT, NOT A
LEGAL REQUIREMENT OR CONDITION OF USE.

TO SUPPORT THE LONG-TERM SUSTAINABILITY OF TAIKO'S BASED ROLLUP STACK AS A
PUBLIC GOOD, THE TAIKO COMMUNITY INVITES PROJECTS THAT BENEFIT FROM TAIKO
SOFTWARE TO CONSIDER CONTRIBUTING BACK TO THE TAIKO DAO.

1. ENCOURAGED SUPPORT
   PROJECTS MAY CHOOSE TO CONTRIBUTE TO THE TAIKO DAO TO HELP FUND CONTINUED
   DEVELOPMENT, SECURITY, AND MAINTENANCE. CONTRIBUTIONS MAY BE MADE IN ETHER
   AND/OR TOKENS.

2. SUGGESTED CONTRIBUTION MODELS (BOTH RECOMMENDED WHERE APPLICABLE)

   (A) REVENUE SHARE: PROJECTS MAY VOLUNTARILY CONTRIBUTE 10% OF PROTOCOL
       REVENUE (E.G., BASE FEES) ON AN ANNUAL BASIS.

   (B) TOKEN ALLOCATION: PROJECTS WITH NATIVE TOKENS MAY ALSO CONTRIBUTE
       A SMALL PORTION OF SUPPLY AS FOLLOWS:
       - TOKEN CREATED > 2 YEARS BEFORE MAINNET GENESIS: NO CONTRIBUTION
       - TOKEN CREATED ≤ 2 YEARS BEFORE MAINNET GENESIS: 1% OF MAX SUPPLY
       - TOKEN CREATED ≤ 1 YEAR BEFORE MAINNET GENESIS: 1.5% OF MAX SUPPLY
       - TOKEN CREATED AFTER MAINNET GENESIS: 2% OF MAX SUPPLY

   CONTRIBUTION DETAILS:
   - ALL CONTRIBUTIONS (ETHER AND TOKENS) SHOULD BE UNLOCKED AND LIQUID
   - SEND TO TAIKO DAO TREASURY: 0x75Ba76403b13b26AD1beC70D6eE937314eeaCD0a
     (controller.taiko.eth)
   - TOKEN CONTRIBUTIONS APPRECIATED WITHIN 6 MONTHS OF PROJECT MAINNET GENESIS
   - PLEASE CONTACT FUND@TAIKO.XYZ TO VERIFY ADDRESS BEFORE SENDING

3. VOLUNTARY NATURE
   THESE GUIDELINES ARE ENTIRELY VOLUNTARY AND DO NOT CREATE ANY LEGAL OR
   CONTRACTUAL OBLIGATION. YOUR USE, COPYING, OR MODIFICATION OF THIS SOFTWARE
   REMAINS GOVERNED EXCLUSIVELY BY THE MIT LICENSE ABOVE.

4. ETHICAL USE
   USERS ARE ENCOURAGED TO APPLY THIS SOFTWARE IN AN ETHICAL, TRANSPARENT,
   AND LAWFUL MANNER CONSISTENT WITH THE PRINCIPLES OF A FAIR AND DECENTRALIZED
   ECOSYSTEM.

FOR MORE INFORMATION OR TO DISCUSS CONTRIBUTIONS:
   EMAIL: FUND@TAIKO.XYZ
   WEB: HTTPS://TAIKO.XYZ
